<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL COOLER AND FILTER - Oil
        Cooler - Filling Crankcase With Oil
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="0">
        <title>Filling Crankcase With Oil</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill the crankcase with 18.5 L (19.5 qt) of oil if the filter has been changed or 17 L (18
                qt) of oil if the filter has not been changed. If the oil cooler was removed or drained of oil, add an
                extra 0.94 L (1 qt) of oil.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start the engine and check for leaks. Fix leaks as needed.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Shut down the engine and check the oil level. Add oil or drain oil as needed to bring the
                oil level within the FULL and ADD marks on the oil level gauge. Do not overfill past the FULL mark.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
